<TITLE> President urges unity for development </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kishoreganj, May 30 (bdnews24.com) President Mohammed Zillur Rahman has urged everyone to forget their differences and work together for the country's development. The president was speaking at a reception on Sunday given in his honour at Kuliarchar Pilot High Cchool premises. The Citizen's Reception Committee convener and Kuliarchar Group chairman Musa Miah presided over the function Zillur said all possible steps would be taken for the development of Kuliarchar, and instructed the authorities to meet different demands of the people including gas connection in the Upazila, uninterrupted power supply, establishment of a polytechnic school and the construction of Kuliarchar-Bhairab bridge. He recalled that his childhood and youth were spent in the area and he was spiritually linked with Kuliarchar. Others who spoke on the occasion, were LGRD minister Syed Ashraful Islam, state minister for liberation war ministry ABM Tajul Islam, MP and president's son Nazmul Hasan and Kuliarchar Upazila chairman Mohammed Jahangir. Ashraful also promised all possible help for the development of Kuliarchar. Tajul said no conspiracy could stop the trial of those who committed crimes against humanity during the 1971 war of independence and promised that Tk 5,000 would be given to 100 freedom fighters who were war-wounded and disadvantaged. The president also inaugurated the Victory Memorial built at a cost of Tk 28 lakh and attended different programmes in Brahmanbaria. bdnew
